Install a java compiler and a run time environment.
Install a certian free relational database management system.
Install a java servlet container.
Get a java database connectivity API and a servlet API.
Compile the program (example given for linux in "compile" file).

Create a database with the free relational database management system called mrknowitall and inside the database
create the tables; t_lines, t_patterns and t_responses. (An example is given below)

	create table t_lines ( flinenum INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY, flines VARBINARY(255) );
	create table t_patterns ( fpatternnum INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY, fpatterns VARBINARY(255) );
	create table t_responses ( fresponsenum INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY, fresponses VARBINARY(255) );

Make sure the servlet API and java database connectivity API is in the servlet container's classpath.
Place compiled classes and mrknowitall.html in the servlet container.
Run the servlet.

Note: May need to create an xml file, an example is given in the file "web.xml".